content: Q2 and Q3 are expected to grow in the high teens as the comps get tougher and the macroeconomic environment worsens a little before accelerating in Q4 into the low 20s once we have lapped our BNPL customers partial volume migration and we begin to lap the impact of all the renewal activity.Q1 gross profit growth is expected to be between 14% and 16% in line with our full year expectations, Q3 should also be similar.
